      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "With $2,300,000 capitalization\nthe Spokane Gas & Fuel Co., com.\nposed of eastern capital, filed ar.\nticles of incorporation yesterday\nwith the county auditor.\n1t is understood that it is mere.\nly a re-incorporation of the old\nSpokane Falls Gas Light Co. for\nthe purpose of taking over the\nUnion Gas Co. of Spokane. The\nSpokane Falls company held the\noperating franchise of the Union\nand the move is said to be for the\npurpose of convenience.\nThe names of five local men-A\ne. Gallagher, Maurice Smith, M. E.\nMack, A. M. Baker and R. r\nRogers-are given in the articles\nof incorporation.\n\n\nThe records show $4,000 shares\nof stock listed at 500 each. There\nare 5000 preferred and 10000 COM\nmon shares."
    }
  ]
